uk.co.saiman.data

Interface ContinuousFunctionDecorator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ContinuousFunction, uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.Copyable<ContinuousFunction>, uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression.Expression<ContinuousFunction>, uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.Observable<uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression.Expression<ContinuousFunction>>, uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.Self<ContinuousFunction>, uk.co.strangeskies.mathematics.expression.SelfExpression<ContinuousFunction>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SampledContinuousFunctionDecorator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CalibratedContinuousFunction, ContinuousFunctionExpression, ContinuousFunctionTransformation, SampledContinuousFunctionTransformation

    public interface ContinuousFunctionDecorator
extends ContinuousFunction
    A partial implementation of a ContinuousFunction decorator, to reduce boilerplate for functions which are in some way mappings of other functions.

      • resample

        default SampledContinuousFunction resample(double startX,
                                           double endX,
                                           int resolvableUnits)
        Description copied from interface: ContinuousFunction
        Sometimes it is useful to linearise a continuous function in order to perform complex processing, or for display purposes. This method provides a linear view of any continuous function. Implementations may remove features which are unresolvable at the given resolution.
        Specified by:
        resample in interface ContinuousFunction
        Parameters:
        startX - The start of the interval we wish to sample over
        endX - The end of the interval we wish to sample over
        resolvableUnits - The minimum resolvable units within the given interval
        Returns:
        A new sampled, linear continuous function roughly equal to the receiver to the requested resolution
